    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check + FR-1A.9</step>
    <step order="1">Create MembershipEndpoints.cs with MapMembershipEndpoints extension</step>
    <step order="2">Implement handler: resolve current user via OBO claims → delegate to MembershipResolverService → return MembershipResponse</step>
    <step order="3">Parse query params (roles, identityTypes, limit, continuationToken)</step>
    <step order="4">Pagination via continuation token (default limit 500)</step>
    <step order="5">Register in Program.cs with .RequireAuthorization()</step>
    <step order="6">Unit + integration tests</step>
    <step order="7">Publish-size delta</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">GET /api/users/me/memberships/sprk_matter returns expected IDs for seeded user (AC-1A.3)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Filters work (roles, identityTypes)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Pagination via continuation token works for &gt;500 memberships</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">401 for unauthenticated; 403 if any future role gate applied</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
  <notes>
    Completed 2026-06-21. Files (new, src): Api/Membership/MembershipEndpoints.cs (~440 lines —
    includes MembershipApiExtensions Add+Map pairing). Files (new, tests):
    tests/.../Api/Membership/MembershipEndpointsTests.cs (18 tests covering auth gate,
    malformed input, query-param → MembershipResolveOptions mapping, ExtractAadObjectId
    + ParseCsv helpers). Files (modified, src): Program.cs (+8 lines: using import +
    AddMembershipApi() call), Infrastructure/DI/EndpointMappingExtensions.cs (+9 lines:
    using import + MapMembershipApi() call + comment block).
    18/18 new tests pass (1s). No regressions: 51/51 related tests still pass
    (JobsEndpoints 11, IdentityNormalization 10, MembershipResolver 12, MembershipResponse 10,
    other Membership-namespace 8). BFF build: 0 errors, 16 pre-existing warnings unchanged.
    Publish size: 44.85 MB compressed (-1.33 MB vs task 020 baseline of 46.18; no NuGet adds).
    CVE check: no new HIGH-severity CVE (Microsoft.Kiota.Abstractions 1.21.2 HIGH unchanged,
    tracked at project level).
    Design decisions:
    - Current-user systemuserid lookup mechanism: INLINE HELPER in MembershipEndpoints.cs
      (ResolveSystemUserIdAsync). Reasons: (a) first BFF surface needing AAD-oid →
      systemuserid (opposite direction from IdentityNormalizationService's systemuserid →
      6-path PersonIdentity); (b) helper is ~30 lines using cached IDataverseService +
      IDistributedCache; (c) introducing a one-use ICurrentUserService would create premature
      abstraction. Documented future extraction path: when a SECOND endpoint needs the
      same direction, extract to Services/Ai/Membership/CurrentUserResolver.cs.
      Cache key: "membership:currentuser:{aadOid:D}" (sibling namespace to
      IdentityNormalizationService's "membership:identity:*"). TTL: 10 min (matches
      identity-normalization cache TTL). Query also filters isdisabled=false to prevent
      disabled-user impersonation.
    - Endpoint registration site: PAIRED Add+Map convention via MembershipApiExtensions
      (in MembershipEndpoints.cs). AddMembershipApi() is currently no-op (resolver is
      registered by MembershipModule.AddMembership from task 033) but reserved for future
      endpoint-specific services (e.g., the extracted CurrentUserResolver). MapMembershipApi()
      delegates to MapMembershipEndpoints(). Both wired UNCONDITIONALLY in Program.cs +
      EndpointMappingExtensions.MapDomainEndpoints per bff-extensions.md §F.1.
    - Query-param parsing: ParseCsv normalizes empty CSV ("roles=" or "roles=,,,") to null
      so MembershipResolverService treats it as "use all" per its MembershipResolveOptions
      contract. limit=0 / limit&lt;0 returns 400; limit&gt;MaxLimit (5000) silently clamps
      to MaxLimit (matches OData top-N clamp convention).
    - Auth model: standard .RequireAuthorization() on MapGroup (no specific policy — any
      authenticated user can query their OWN memberships, never another user's). Defensive
      re-check of oid claim after RequireAuthorization in case a test or filter override
      bypasses the policy (matches PrecedentAdminEndpoints precedent). 401 (not 403) when
      Dataverse has no matching systemuser row — the token authenticates an unknown
      identity rather than denying a known one.
    - includeRelated passthrough: endpoint surfaces options.IncludeRelated to the resolver
      verbatim. Phase 1A MembershipResolverService ignores it; task 054 activates Phase 1D
      transitive expansion without touching MembershipEndpoints.cs.
    - Test fixture: dedicated MembershipEndpointsTestFixture (NOT shared with AdminJobsTestFixture
      or CustomWebAppFactory) because tests need per-call AAD oid selection via X-Test-Oid
      header — sibling fixtures hardcode either SystemAdmin or a fixed user id which would
      mask the oid-claim extraction path. MockBehavior.Strict on IMembershipResolverService
      surfaces any unexpected call as test failure; MockBehavior.Loose on IDataverseService
      allows seeded-by-test query setup without needing to stub every unrelated call.
    AC verification (unit-level — integration AC-1A.3 + AC-1A.5 deferred to P4 UAT per task brief):
    - 200 + MembershipResponse for authenticated user: ✅ (GetMyMemberships_Returns200_...).
    - Filters work (roles, identityTypes): ✅ (MapsRolesAndIdentityTypesCsv_ToResolverOptions).
    - Pagination via continuationToken: ✅ (MapsLimitAndContinuationToken_ToResolverOptions).
    - 401 unauthenticated: ✅ (Returns401_WhenUnauthenticated).
    - Filters mapped correctly to MembershipResolveOptions: ✅ (6 mapping tests).
    - includeRelated passed through: ✅ (MapsIncludeRelated_ToResolverOptions_ForPhase1DPassthrough).
    adr-check (self): PASS — ADR-001 (Minimal API extension method), ADR-008 (.RequireAuthorization
    on MapGroup, no global middleware, RFC 7807 ProblemDetails), ADR-009 (Redis 10-min TTL
    matches IdentityNormalizationService), ADR-010 (no premature interface — helper is inline
    with documented extraction path), ADR-028 (oid claim canonical + cross-ref via
    azureactivedirectoryobjectid), ADR-029 (publish-size -1.33 MB).
    bff-extensions §A/§F/§F.1: PASS — Placement Justification documented in publish-size note,
    ADRs cited above, publish-size measured + within ceiling, no new CRUD→AI dep,
    feature-module DI (MembershipApiExtensions Add+Map pairing), unconditional registration
    on both sides, 18 unit tests cover new behavior.
    Not committed per task brief. Notes: notes/bff-publish-size-task035.md.
  </notes>
</task>
